 tablespoon of the reserved crab filling along bottom edge of the pastry sheet. Fold in both sides of pastry and roll up to form a brik (neat rectangle shape). Set aside on a plate and continue with remaining filo sheets and filling (makes 8 briks in total)."},{"content":"Line a plate with paper towel and set aside. Place a large frying pan over medium-heat and add oil (approx. 1 cm deep). Working in batches, fry briks for 2-3 minutes, turning once, or until golden brown on both sides. Carefully remove from oil and transfer to prepared plate to drain. Serve warm with reserved salsa."}],"hintsAndTricks":["You can cut filo sheets into halves and make 16 smaller briks if desired."],"basicInfo":["easy","55m","55m","8 portions"]}